
** Alter Session

  - Needs to be assigned with the grant command. 

  - SQL> grant alter session to <user>;

  - For the sql trace setting it might be better to use the various
    dbms packages as dbms_support (not enabled at default)

** Examples

<example>
  SQL> alter session set SQL_TRACE true;
</example>

<example>
  --  4 bind variables
  --  8 wait events
  -- 12 both
  SQL> alter session set events '10046
       trace name context forever, level 12';
  SQL> alter session set events '10046
       trace name context off';
</example>

<example>
  -- This sets the european week calculation. But not the nls_sort
  -- parameter. This parameter can only be set in the init ora file
  -- or with alter session.
  SQL> alter session set nls_territory = germany;
</example>
